The paper deals with a problem in graph theory and approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of heuristics and approximation algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The study of network generation models suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of linear programming suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
